        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>A bunion is characterized by a prominent bump on the inside of the foot around the big toe joint, caused by a bone protruding towards the inside of the foot. As the big toe moves toward the smaller toes, it can end up resting under or over the second toe, leading to a condition known as overlapping toes.<br/><br/>Symptoms of bunions include inflammation, swelling, and soreness on the side surface of the big toe, often causing improper walking.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
